==============================================================================================================================================================================================================================================================================
README.md



# React Movie Review App

The React Movie Review App is a dynamic, responsive web application that allows users to browse, search, filter, and rate movies using data fetched from The Movie Database (TMDB) API. Users can view detailed information about each movie and rate them using a star-based system, with ratings persisted in the browser's localStorage.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Setup & Installation](#setup--installation)
- [Core Concepts](#core-concepts)
  - [State Management](#state-management)
  - [API Integration](#api-integration)
  - [Routing](#routing)
  - [Styling](#styling)
- [Key Components & Files](#key-components--files)
- [Extending the App](#extending-the-app)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [License](#license)

## Features

- Fetches movie data from the TMDB API
- Displays movies in a responsive grid layout with individual movie cards
- Search bar for finding movies by title
- Filter bar for filtering movies by genre, year, and minimum rating
- View detailed movie information, including description, cast, and release details
- Add and update star-based ratings for movies (persisted in localStorage)
- Responsive design for optimal viewing on all devices

## Project Structure

The project is organized into the following directory structure:

